external_knowledge:
- "shining stars" refers to employees with performance scores >= 90;
- "illuminate" metaphorically represents the department where the employee works;
- "radiant performance scores" refers to the high performance scores >= 90;
- "shadows where they can grow even brighter" symbolizes the areas for improvement in the performance review.

- "secret identities" refers to usernames; 
- "gateways they guard" refers to role names; 
- "last time they peeked through the door" refers to the last login date; 
- "last time they reset their keys" refers to the last password change date; 
- "lone voyager" refers to the user with account_id 1 in the ship's log (user_accounts table).

- "small gardens nurturing fewer than 11 blossoms": refers to departments with 10 or fewer employees;
- "sun shine on their training sessions": indicates that the feedback received was very positive (rating above 5);
- "celestial number 5": metaphorically represents the threshold of 5 for the rating;
- "the period from the beginning of February to the end of March in the year 2023": the specific time frame when the feedback was submitted.

